Since the lex Cornelia of Sulla (BC 81) the indicia had been in the hands of the Senate, as they had been before the lex Sempronia of C Gracchus (BC 122). The lenity shewn in dealing with the maladministration of provincial go- vernors brought on an agitation sor reform in the constitution of the courts, which had now reached its height. Cicero dexterously works upon the jury, seeking to put them on their good behaviour. But, notwithstanding the upright- ness of the jury which tried Verres, the transfer was brought about in this very year by the law of the Praetor L Aurelius Cotta.
